<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Contains a default mapping of remote keys to MP2 keys.
  For each key mapping to be interpreted by MP2, there must be a RemoteKeyCode element.
  The Code attribute contains the code representing the key pressed. The Func_Name attribute contains
  a reference to a MP2 key or secreen. The prefix (S: or P:) determines if the key is a special (S:) or printable (P:) key.
  The suffix is the special key name or the printable key's character. The prefix (Home: or Config:) determines if the 
  screen is a home (Home:) or configuration (Config:) screen. The suffix is the name of the screen.

  Each key code may only be mapped once (i.e. a key code given in the Code attribute may only be at most once).
  It is not necessary to add a RemoteKeyCode entry for each key code, but it is recommended to do so. If a remote key
  should not be mapped to an MP2 key, the special key None (S:None) can be used.
-->
<ArrayOfRemoteKeyCode xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
